### VoiceTask Backend API Requests

### SETUP: Copy your Supabase JWT and set it as @token variable
### Get JWT from: Supabase Dashboard → Auth → Users → (select user) → Generate JWT

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = your-supabase-jwt-here

### Health Check (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


### ========== USERS API ==========

### Create or Update User (JIT provisioning)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "picture": "https://example.com/photo.jpg",
  "timezone": "Asia/Kolkata"
}

### Update User Profile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "timezone": "America/New_York"
}


### ========== VOICE API ==========

### Transcribe Audio File (in-memory, no persistence)
### Create a test.m4a file or use any audio file
POST {{baseUrl}}/voice/transcribe
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="audio"; filename="test.m4a"
Content-Type: audio/mp4

< ./test.m4a
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### Extract Task from Transcript Text
POST {{baseUrl}}/voice/extract
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Call mom tomorrow at 6pm to discuss the new project",
  "timezone": "Asia/Kolkata"
}


### ========== TASKS API ==========

### List All Tasks (optional: ?status=PENDING)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List Pending Tasks Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks?status=PENDING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Single Task
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create Task with Future Due Date (will schedule QStash reminder)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Call mom",
  "description": "Discuss the new project",
  "dueAt": "2026-05-05T18:00:00Z",
  "reminderOffsetMinutes": 15,
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "transcript": "Call mom tomorrow at 6pm to discuss the new project"
}

### Create Task without Due Date
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Buy groceries",
  "description": "Milk, eggs, bread",
  "priority": "LOW"
}

### Update Task (reschedules QStash if dueAt/reminderOffset changed)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Call mom - Updated",
  "status": "COMPLETED"
}

### Mark Task as Completed (cancels QStash reminder)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "COMPLETED"
}

### Delete Task (cancels QStash reminder)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ========== DEVICES API ==========

### Register Device for Push Notifications
### Call this on app sign-in with the FCM token
POST {{baseUrl}}/devices
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fcmToken": "cMzR6n5fwQw:APA91bF0abcdef123456...",
  "platform": "android"
}

### Unregister Device (call on sign-out)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/devices/cMzR6n5fwQw:APA91bF0abcdef123456...
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ========== WEBHOOKS (QStash Internal) ==========
### These are called by QStash, not by your app
### QStash verifies signature with UPSTASH_CURRENT_SIGNING_KEY + UPSTASH_NEXT_SIGNING_KEY

### POST /webhooks/qstash (fired when task is due)
### Headers: Upstash-Signature: <signature>
### Body: { "taskId": "..." }
### This endpoint sends FCM notifications to all user devices
